    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-14T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-14T10:00:00-05:00" n="127"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d127">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.001 <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt, F.
                        D.</persName>/9453½: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SLA1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the President, the Secretary of State, and the
                        Under Secretary of State</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SERJ1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stettinius</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d127fn1">On November 17, 1943, the White House
                        Map Room telegraphed a paraphrase of this message to <persName
                            corresp="#p_GDW1">Greer</persName>, “to be held for delivery to the
                        President upon arrival at Oran.”</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-14T17:00:00+02:00"
                            >November 14, 1943—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1869. Most secret for the President, the Secretary and the Under Secretary.</p>
                <p>In expressing his keen pleasure with President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1"
                        >Roosevelt</persName>’s letter of October 26 to President <persName
                        corresp="#p_II1">Inönü</persName>,<note n="2" xml:id="d127fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_43">p. 43</ref>.</note> the
                    Minister for Foreign Affairs<note n="3" xml:id="d127fn3">
                        <persName corresp="#p_MN1">Numan Menemencioğlu</persName>.</note> remarked
                    to me last night that <persName corresp="#p_II1">Inönü</persName> would be
                    delighted to meet our President and that if President <persName
                        corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> could not be persuaded to visit
                    Turkey, he would be more than pleased to go to meet him should he visit any
                    other part of the Near East.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SLA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
